    "Given a word sequence X = {x 1, x 2,..., x n }, a trigger word a and the corresponding label sequence Y = {y 1, y 2,..., y n }, each word x i corresponds to a event type label.",
    "Figure 2 illustrates the mapping of words to event labels.",
    "The \"O\" type is utilized to indicate words that do not belong to any event type, referred to as non-triggers.",
    "Additionally, in this paper, each sentence is restricted to having only one trigger word and one associated event type.",
    "3.2 N-Way-K-Shot Learning Few-shot learning includes two stages: training and testing."
